text: California Dreams is an American teen sitcom that aired on NBC. It was part of the network's Saturday morning block, TNBC. The series aired from September 12, 1992 to December 14, 1996. Created by writers Brett Dewey and Ronald B. Solomon, and executive produced by Peter Engel, all known for their work on Saved by the Bell, the series centers on the friendships of a group of teenagers who form the fictional titular band.
